The White House Office of the Press Secretary released a readout of a roundtable discussion between Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism Lisa O. Monaco, Assistant to the President and Deputy National Security Advisor Avril D. Haines, human rights and civil liberties advocates, and legal experts. The meeting aimed to address transparency issues concerning counterterrorism operations and the use of force by the United States. Ms. Monaco and Ms. Haines expressed the Administration's dedication to providing the public with as much information as possible regarding these operations.